Here are some natural methods you might explore to manage your infant's fever:
1. Immerse your baby in a tub of warm (not hot) water for about 20 minutes during a power outage or emergency situation, which can help cool their body (this simple technique is outlined in traditional remedy guides);
2. Use a warm compress made from wet towels to relax the muscles and ease discomfort;
3. Clothing-free cooling can be effective too - you might try keeping your baby in different forms of clothing to see what's most comfortable for their body throughout the day.

If you're unable to manage the situation at home, it's completely normal and reasonable to consider taking your baby to the hospital emergency room for medical assistance when traditional remedies aren't accessible or effective. There's no need to feel guilty about exploring these alternatives when it makes sense for your family's health and well-being, even if that means something might seem a bit unorthodox.
